race.comment: PETIT ARTISTE (7) resumes. She didn't win last time in but ran in some strong races, fourth in a good 2yo race fresh last time in before running second to speedy filly Esha. She's largely contested stakes races and looks well placed in this. NIMBUSTWOTHOUSAND (3) was okay first up at Cranbourne over 955m, just beaten for speed there. He'll be better over further again but has the ability to be finishing over the top. NOT SURPRISED (8) resumes. She won her only start last campaign and is open to further improvement at just her fifth start. ETERNAL DARKNESS (5) bounced back last start following a disappointing run at Caulfield two back. Maps nicely and can go one better without surprising.
